{"title_page": "Shobha Nihalani", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name        = Shobha Nihalani\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = 230px\n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place = [[]], [[India]]\n| occupation  = Novelist\n| nationality = Indian\n| website = {{URL|http://www.shobhanihalani.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Shobha Nihalani''' is is an [[India|Indian]] [[author]] of adventure and thriller novels: ''The Silent Monument, the NINE trilogy, Unresolved - A psychological thriller, Trikon \u2013 a medical sci-fi thriller,'' and ''The Blue Jade.'' Recently, she wrote two non-fiction books, a biography of a humanitarian and spiritual leader \u2013 ''Dada Vaswani \u2013 A Life in Spirituality.'' And a memoir, ''A Gift from Above \u2013 Haresh and Harini\u2019s\u00a0 Journey in Adoption.'' Her debut novel, ''Karmic Blues,'' was translated and published in Denmark.\n\nIn her latest novel, ''The Blue Jade,'' Nihalani, brings to you a captivating story about historical artifacts falling into the wrong hands. ''TheBlue Jade'' is a thrilling adventure in the murky world of black-market art set against the historical backdrop of the legendary princess-saint Mirabai.\n\nHer ''NINE'' [[trilogy]] was a unique interpretation of the Unknown Nine legend. Unlike the original legend, her interpretation reveals some members of the Unknown Nine to be women. The Nine trilogy weaves past and future events to reveal how the Nine have guided humanity toward its destiny. <ref>http://www.penguinbooksindia.com/en/content/shobha-nihalani:<br>''Books by Shobha Nihalani.''</ref><ref>http://www.ibnlive.com/news/books/my-book-nine-is-a-mix-of-facts-and-fiction-shobha-nihalani-622422.html:<br>''Q&A with Shobha Nihalani.''</ref> Her debut novel, ''Karmic Blues'', was first published in [[Danish language|Danish]] by EC-Edition in 2008, although it was originally written in [[English language|English]]. \n\nAccording to her website she has previously worked as a [[freelance]] [[journalist]], [[copywriter]], [[bookkeeper]], English [[teacher]] and [[salesperson]]. She recently co-wrote the screenplay for [[Squad (2020)|Squad]] with Director [[Nilesh Sahay|Nilesh Sahay.]]\n\n==Personal life==\nNihalani currently lives with her family in [[Hong Kong]] and often visits India.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n;Official\n* [http://www.shobhanihalani.com/ Shobha Nihalani website]\n* [http://penguin.co.in/?s=shobha+nihalani Shobha Nihalani at penguin]\n* [http://www.jaicobooks.com/j/j_searchtry.asp?selcat=author_name&keyword=shobha+Nihalani Shobha Nihalani at jaicobooks]\n* [http://indiaresearchpress.com/authordetails/author-A08C7C73-EC24-4B2F-8F33-8E3F2BA4AB37 Shobha Nihalani at indiaresearchpress]\n* [http://www.ec-edition.dk/?s=shobha+nihalani Shobha Nihalani at ec-edition]\n* [http://www.hachetteindia.com/Search_Result.aspx?searchfor=shobha%20nihalani Shobha Nihalani at hachetteindia]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nihalani, Shoba}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong writers]]\n[[Category:Indian fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Indian thriller writers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{India-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name        = Shobha Nihalani\n| image       = \n| imagesize   = 230px\n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place = [[]], [[India]]\n| occupation  = Novelist\n| nationality = Indian\n| website = {{URL|http://www.shobhanihalani.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Shobha Nihalani''' is an [[India]]n [[author]] known for her  [[thriller novel|thriller]] and [[fantasy novel|fantasy]] [[novel]]s; ''The Silent Monument'' and the ''Nine'' [[trilogy]].\nHer trilogy is a unique interpretation of the Unknown Nine legend. Unlike the original legend, her interpretation reveals some members of the Unknown Nine to be women. The Nine trilogy weaves past and future events to reveal how the Nine have guided humanity toward its destiny. <ref>http://www.penguinbooksindia.com/en/content/shobha-nihalani:<br>''Books by Shobha Nihalani.''</ref><ref>http://www.ibnlive.com/news/books/my-book-nine-is-a-mix-of-facts-and-fiction-shobha-nihalani-622422.html:<br>''Q&A with Shobha Nihalani.''</ref> Her debut novel, ''Karmic Blues'', was first published in [[Danish language|Danish]] by EC-Edition in 2008, although it was originally written in [[English language|English]]. According to her website she has previously worked as a [[freelance]] [[journalist]], [[copywriter]], [[bookkeeper]], English [[teacher]] and [[salesperson]]. She recently co-wrote the screenplay for [[Squad (2020)|Squad]] with Director [[Nilesh Sahay|Nilesh Sahay.]]\n\n==Personal life==\nNihalani currently lives with her family in [[Hong Kong]] and often visits India.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n;Official\n* [http://www.shobhanihalani.com/ Shobha Nihalani website]\n* [http://penguin.co.in/?s=shobha+nihalani Shobha Nihalani at penguin]\n* [http://www.jaicobooks.com/j/j_searchtry.asp?selcat=author_name&keyword=shobha+Nihalani Shobha Nihalani at jaicobooks]\n* [http://indiaresearchpress.com/authordetails/author-A08C7C73-EC24-4B2F-8F33-8E3F2BA4AB37 Shobha Nihalani at indiaresearchpress]\n* [http://www.ec-edition.dk/?s=shobha+nihalani Shobha Nihalani at ec-edition]\n* [http://www.hachetteindia.com/Search_Result.aspx?searchfor=shobha%20nihalani Shobha Nihalani at hachetteindia]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nihalani, Shoba}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Hong Kong writers]]\n[[Category:Indian fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Indian thriller writers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{India-writer-stub}}\n", "name_user": "LipBhu", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updates in her list of books written", "